This paper deals with probabilistic formulations and their relevance to acquiring probabilistic knowledge from human experts. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses belief networks, which are commonly used in machine learning and data analysis, further supporting the likelihood of cs.AI. The paper also deals with probability and statistics, which are relevant to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Information Theory (cs.IT).
